3 Looking for candy? Well you came to the right place. This candy shop has just about anything you're looking for in a candy. From chocolates to fruit candys to gummys and pixy sticks. I'm a huge fan of gummy bears and I love the white chocolate covered gummy bears....can you say yummmmy! As soon as I walked in, I instantly noticed the worlds biggest gummy bear and gummy worm. Man I sure wanted to get it, but I just couldn't imagine scarfing down such huge amounts of candy. I haven't seen any other place that carried this item, I just wanted to get it so I can display it, but then again I couldn't imagine how much of a waste it'd be to have a gummy bear just lying around uneaten. Well this place is cool and all but I really don't like sweets as much as it sounds, but gummy bears RULE! It is a bit expensive though, but well worth it if you're a candy fanatic.
4 There used to be so many of these stores around town, but this just might be the last one still standing. Located on the upper level, just a few store spaces down from Macy's. Price- $2.99 per 1/4 lb., $11.99 per 1 lb. Chocolates, M & M's station, and Sugar-Free are situated along the left side of the wall. You can also find gummies, novelty plush animals, and other goodies here.    Great place to get your sweet on. We don't come to this mall a whole lot, but when we do, 9 times out of 10, we'll drop by. Usually, the cashier is an older woman in lively spirits.
4 $2.99 per 1/4 pound. This store's candy is arranged by type and color- just noticed that the last time we were here, on sunday. The left side has chocolates- like dark chocolate bark, M & M's in different colors (customize), and sugar-free candy, as well as the cashier counter. The middle has seasonal/christmas candy- two sided. The front right side has red candy- like boston-baked beans- mmm, and not the boxed kind, 'cause these are bigger. There is an assortment of candy on the right side, middle- like the blue sour coke gummies (one of my favorites). Against the back wall, are the novelties, like metal lunch boxes (hello kitty, candy, etc.), and the gummies too, worms, bears, sharks, coke bottles (just about every kind too)- white chocolate bark is here too.
